      "content": "These new federal environmental regulations are primarily designed to force small-scale manufacturers to adopt expensive compliance technologies, which will inevitably lead to higher operational costs and reduced competitiveness. The main concerns for these businesses include the immediate financial strain from retrofitting facilities and the long-term risk of being forced out of the market if they cannot afford the mandated upgrades. While the regulations aim to protect the environment, they disproportionately burden small enterprises that lack the capital reserves of larger corporations, effectively accelerating their decline.",
