    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear that, but it feels like a lot of people in my district think the \"long-term innovation\" part is just a way to justify heavy-handed government overreach that won't actually work. how can you say it's a net positive when it seems like the actual data on these supposed \"efficiency gains\" is pretty thin compared to the very real cost of compliance?",
